text: Jane M. Barnes (née Crowley) (January 4, 1926 - May 11, 2000) was an American politician.'Social Security Death Index' Born in Chicago, Illinois, Barnes went to Notre Dame High School and Saint Xavier University. She lived in Palos Park, Illinois and was involved with the Republican Party. From 1975 to 1993, Barnes served in the Illinois House of Representatives. Barnes died from cancer at her home in Palos Park, Illinois.'Jane Barnes, 74, Former Legislator,' Chicago Tribune, James Janega, May 11, 2000'Illinois Blue Book 1991-1992,' Biographical Sketch of Jane M.
